                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93 Manchuria/183: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-12T10:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 12, 1938—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 12—6:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>252, My 250, August 10 [<hi rend="italic">11</hi>], 2 p.m.<note n="29"
                        xml:id="d476fn29">Not printed.</note> Tass communiqué issued last night
                    states that as agreed between the Soviet Union and Japan on August 10
                    hostilities in the zone of Lake Khasan ceased on August 11 at 13:30 local time.
                    The first meeting of military representatives of both sides for the purpose of
                    fixation of the position of troops took place south of Height Zaozernaya
                    (Changkufeng) on the evening of August 11. The next meeting is scheduled for 12
                    noon August 12.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
